e in pre-Confederation Canada. The aftermath of the contest is also explored, including changes to the plans, the problem of costs, the critical reception of the buildings, and their place in the aesthetics of the time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArchitecture publiquexConcoursxHistoirex19e sièclexOntarioxOttawa. 0aArchitecturex19e sièclexCanada. 0aArchitecturexCompetitionsxHistoryx19th centuryxCanada. 0aArchitecturexCompetitionszCanadaxHistoryy19th century. 0aArchitecture, Modernx19th century. 0aArchitecture, Moderny19th century. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356496140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773564961423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773564961/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles